Sentencas: Perovskite-structure La0.75Sr0.5Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-delta (LSCM) powders were prepared using a simple combustion process.
Titulo: Performance of La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ perovskite-structure anode material at lanthanum gallate electrolyte for IT-SOFC running on ethanol fuel

Sentencas: Thermal analysis was carried out on the perovskite precursor to investigate the oxide-phase formation.
Titulo: Performance of La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ perovskite-structure anode material at lanthanum gallate electrolyte for IT-SOFC running on ethanol fuel

Sentencas: The structural phase of the powders was determined by X-ray diffraction.
Titulo: Performance of La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ perovskite-structure anode material at lanthanum gallate electrolyte for IT-SOFC running on ethanol fuel

Sentencas: These results showed that the decomposition of the precursors occurs in a two-step reaction and temperatures higher than 1100 degrees C are required for these decomposition reactions.
Titulo: Performance of La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ perovskite-structure anode material at lanthanum gallate electrolyte for IT-SOFC running on ethanol fuel

Sentencas: For the electrochemical characterization, LSCM anode materials and (Pr0.7Ca0.3)(0.9)MnO3 (PCM) cathode materials were screen-printed on two sides of dense La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.8Mg0.2O3 (LSGM) electrolyte layers prepared by tape casting with a thickness of about 600 mu m, respectively.
Titulo: Performance of La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ perovskite-structure anode material at lanthanum gallate electrolyte for IT-SOFC running on ethanol fuel

Sentencas: The morphology of the screen-printed La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-delta perovskite thick films (65 mu m) was investigated by field emission scanning electron microscope and showed a porous microstructure.
Titulo: Performance of La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ perovskite-structure anode material at lanthanum gallate electrolyte for IT-SOFC running on ethanol fuel

Sentencas: In addition, fuel cell tests were carried out using humidified hydrogen or ethanol stream as fuel and oxygen as oxidant.
Titulo: Performance of La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ perovskite-structure anode material at lanthanum gallate electrolyte for IT-SOFC running on ethanol fuel

Sentencas: The performance of the conventional electrolyte-supported cell LSCM/LSGM/PCM while operating on humidified hydrogen was modest with a maximum power density of 165, 99 and 62 mW cm(-2) at 850, 800 and 750 degrees C, respectively, the corresponding values for the cell while operating on ethanol stream was 160, 101 and 58 mW cm(-2), respectively.
Titulo: Performance of La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ perovskite-structure anode material at lanthanum gallate electrolyte for IT-SOFC running on ethanol fuel

Sentencas: Cell stability tests indicate no significant degradation in performance has been observed after 60 h of cell testing when LSCM anode was exposed to ethanol steam at 750 degrees C, suggesting that carbon deposition was limited during cell operation.
Titulo: Performance of La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ perovskite-structure anode material at lanthanum gallate electrolyte for IT-SOFC running on ethanol fuel
